2.
    a.
        i.
            Metals are malleable because they have ordered and regular layers of positive cations which can slide freely over each other without much resistance.
        ii.
            Metals are good conductors of electricity because they have a sea of delocalised electrons which are free to move to carry charge and conduct electricity.
    b.
        Extraction using carbon is most suitable as electrolysis is expensive. Electrolysis is used when the metal is more reactive than carbon as you cannot extract using carbon in that case, but Iron is less reactive than carbon, so extraction using carbon can be used, which is cheaper.
    c.
        The student could add sodium hydroxide to a sample of each solution. The Iron (II) sulfate will produce green precipitate whereas the Iron (III) sulfate will produce brown precipitate.
